HEADWORD: Strombuliform
<hw>Strom*bu"li*form</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>strombulus</ets>, dim. of <ets>strombus + -form</ets>. See
<er>Strombus</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Formed or
shaped like a top.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Coiled into the shape of a screw
or a helix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

